##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "parserNumberWithUnits.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

$side = random(2,10,1);
$sideU = NumberWithUnits("$side cm");

$volume = $side**3;
$baseArea = $side**2;
$baseAreaU = NumberWithUnits("$baseArea cm^2");
$ans = NumberWithUnits("$volume cm^3");

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

A cube's side length is [`[$sideU]`]. Its volume is [_____________]{$ans}. 

[@KeyboardInstructions(q!(Use [|cm^3|]* for cubic centimeters.)!)@]**

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

A cube's volume formula is:

    [`` \text{cube volume} = \text{side length}^{3} ``]

Using this formula, we have:

    [``\begin{aligned}
       \text{cube volume}
       & = \text{side length}^{3} \\
       & = [$side]^{3} \\
       & = [$ans]
     \end{aligned}``]

    Don't forget the volume unit [`\textrm{cm}^{3}`].

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
